org.netbeans.api.intent

Class IntentAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.netbeans.api.intent.IntentAction

  • public final class IntentAction
extends Object
    Actual action for an Intent. Pair of an Intent and one of its handlers.
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute(@NullAllowed
                    Callback callback)
        Execute the intent action. The operation will be run asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        callback - Callback object that will be notified when the execution completes. If callback is null, the result will be ignored.

      • execute

        @NonNull
public Future<Object> execute()
        Execute the intent action. The operation will be run asynchronously.

        If the result is ignored, it's recommended to use intentAction.execute(null);

        Returns:
        Future for result of the action. The type of result depends on implementation of chosen intent handler, it can be null.

      • getDisplayName

        @NonNull
public String getDisplayName()
        Get display name of this action.
        Returns:
        The localized display name.

      • getIcon

        @NonNull
public String getIcon()
        Get icon of this action.
        Returns:
        Some resource identifier, e.g. icon id, path or URI. Depends on the platform. If not available, empty string is returned.
